⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Catherine de' Medici
node N1 · N1 · ⟦Catherine de' Medici:N1:057b57⟧

WHO   — Catherine de' Medici — the royal patron of the prophet
WHAT  — The royal hand behind the prophet — the patron who gave the seer of Salon his standing, had him cast the horoscopes of her sons, and shielded his reputation against the doubters of the court.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a queen ruling through frail boy-kings in an age of war and faction sought every counsel, earthly and astral; because the astrologer's veiled assurances steadied a precarious throne; because patronage of the famous seer was itself a kind of power.
HOW   — By summoning Nostradamus to the court at Blois and Paris, by commissioning the horoscopes of her children, by granting him title and favor, and by binding the prophet's fame to the fortunes of the Valois crown.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I ruled through sons and shadows, and I bid the seer cast their stars — for a throne held by a regent takes counsel from every heaven it can.

